      "span_text": "heterozygous females have three and are trichromatic ). (That is, heterozygous females are both retinally and functionally trichromatic.) Mice are normally dichromatic, but if an allele for a third cone pigment is inserted on the X-chromosome the heterozygous females will be trichromatic (Jacobs et al. 2007 )."
